You are right about Cookie..he is an extremist!<br>
He is extremely factual..honest and devoted to the straight line. He doesn't compromise on certain things.. on hardly anything to accomodate vile slackards.  He doesn't confuse the idea of tact with the idea of laying down one's values so others can be partially correct.  He believes in the law, survival of the fittest, and orients himself toward being fit..mentally, physically, and spiritualy.  He doesn't pray on the weak because he is strong.. but chooses to confront those who perpetuate weakness or those who choose to pray on the unfortunate.<br>
Those who are heavy into reality often offend the idealist daydreamer.  It is okay to master your dreams but not okay to let your dreams master you.  There are those who sit on their asses and jaw about freedom and there are those who will get up and die for it.(Crude bastards aren't they!)<br><br>
It is Cook Barela who is trying to get a dialogue between former enemy soldiers and Viet Nam vets going.  It is Cook Barela who posts pertinant data of interest.  It is Cook Barela who is probably the most complete opposite of Jellyfish Spatz.. therefore his main target.<br>
Cookie is not always polished in his presentations.. an understatement..but you never have to wonder about his views or position.  I have more tolerance for guys that bend nails than those who never pick up the hammer.<br><br>
There is no such thing as being kinda pregnant..you either are..or you're not!<br><br>
When my first born came home with a torn shirt or bloody nose acquired in the act of defending himself, he was not sent to his room.  He was not lauded for fighting nor chastized for standing his ground.  I checked him over, washed his face and sent him out to play with the good boys and the bad boys.<br>
You can send Barry Spatz to hell or the zoo.. but don't send my brother Cookie to his room.<br>
We don't need any backroom chit chat to passively stroke a Combat Marine.. this is not a Tuperware party for seductive, grinning compromise to keep the peace.  I embrace the thought that no man can tell another man what to do..we reach common ideas..common goals and a brotherhood because of common values that we share.<br>
I was once chastized by my commander (MOM) for being a little too reckless in extracting a wounded private under fire.  I told my commander (MOM) to respectfully kiss my ass.<br>
Thanks for you presence and your sane views on the insane, but watch your step even though we love you.<br><br>
